    <stitle>Spanish - Gu&#237;a para Localizaci&#243;n de Fallas del Sistema El&#233;ctrico - 3200, 4200, 4300, 4400,
        7300, 7400, 7500, 8500, 8600 - STEERING COLUMN ASSEMBLY, STANDARD - 5000, 9000 CONV. - MAINTENANCE
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>MAINTENANCE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="pm" graphiccount="0">
            <title>END YOKE PINCH BOLTS</title>
            <para>The pinch bolts and nuts on the lower steering column end yokes should be checked for tightness
                annually or every 50,000 miles (80,000 kilometers), whichever comes first. Tighten as specified in the
                <hotlnk document="s05011_10.xml" xrefid="hl0501101">TORQUE CHART
                    <xref refid="hl0501101"/>
                </hotlnk>
                . DO NOT OVERTIGHTEN.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The upper steering column end yoke and the upper steering column shaft are a welded assembly.
                        Only the lower column and steering gear end yokes have a pinch bolt assembly.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
